Description: Location data is presented in a map within the publication, coordinates were extracted by georeferencing the map into Google Earth and digitizing points of interest.
Typical accuracy: Up to tens of meters, depending on how precise is the originally published map.

Description: A federal, state, or local government agency website hosting a database of well log or core log descriptions and/or metadata.
Location provided as a grid reference to a national map. Conversion should be made to WGS 1984 decimal degrees.
